---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import siteData from '../data/site.json';

const page = siteData.pages.books;
const styles = [
  'assets/css/tokens.css',
  'assets/css/interior-base.css',
  'assets/css/layout.css',
  'assets/css/components.css',
  'assets/css/books.css',
];
---
<Base
  title={page.title}
  description={page.description}
  canonical={page.canonical}
  subtitle={page.subtitle}
  eyebrow={page.eyebrow}
  introKicker={page.introKicker}
  introTitle={page.introTitle}
  introText={page.introText}
  currentNav={page.currentNav}
  brandMode="editorial"
  styles={styles}
>
  <div class="stack">
    <section class="reading-width stack" aria-label="Publishing programs">
      <p class="section-copy">The catalog is the program. Three arms, each making a different argument about what Southern writing is owed.</p>

      <article class="card stack">
        <h2 class="section-heading">SEXP</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">Original Southern fiction, poetry, and novella. Work that does not require the trade apparatus to make its case. SEXP publishes work at the formal & spiritual extremity of the tradition: not regional color, not pastoral sentiment, not the workshop aesthetic that has gutted American fiction for forty years. What remains when the genre conventions and the market expectations are removed: the thing the work actually is. Very few entries.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card stack">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Library of the Southern Civilization</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">Not antiquarianism. The Southern tradition has been systematically misfiled: by Northern editorial taste, by academic rehabilitation programs that defang what they canonize, by commercial publishing that has never understood it. The Library recovers texts that deserve continued circulation and makes them available in editions that treat them as what they are.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card stack">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Translation</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">The logic behind the selection is simple: these traditions have sustained formal and spiritual registers that Anglo-American publishing has spent decades flattening. The series brings across what has been allowed to remain difficult, without apology and without the translator's note that explains away the difficulty.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <nav class="filter-tabs" id="books-filter" aria-label="Filter by series"></nav>
    <div class="helper-text" id="books-status" role="status" aria-live="polite">Loading catalog...</div>
    <section class="books-list" id="books-list" aria-label="Books catalog"></section>
    <div class="reading-width">
      <div class="catalog-actions">
        <a class="button" href="/about">Rights or press inquiries</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/submit">Submission inquiries</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Fragment slot="scripts">
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/site-shell.js" type="module"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/books-page.js" type="module"></script>
  </Fragment>
</Base>
